This module mainly defines the good coupling of the illumination in the single-pixel microscope by adequately integrating the DMD into the system. The use of DMD-based optical systems represents a rather challenging alignment process. This device consists of an array of independent micro-sized mirrors with controllable tilt angle states. The DMD has three states; when it is not energized, the tilt angle of the mirrors is 0°, which is called the flat state. On the other hand, when it is energized, the micromirrors flip between two tilt angles, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
